In a mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup flour, confectioners' sugar and salt. Cut in butter as for pastry. Pat into a 6-in. x 10-in. baking pan. Bake crust at 375 degrees F for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, beat the eggs, sugar, remaining flour and baking powder. Fold in rhubarb and spread over baked crust. Return to the oven and bake for 35-40 minutes. Cool. Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.